The image presents a graph with the x-axis labeled "Digital input code" and the y-axis labeled "Differential linearity error". The graph displays the relationship between the digital input code (DAC) and the differential linearity error, represented by a purple line on the graph. The x-axis shows the DAC values from 0 to 40, while the y-axis represents the corresponding errors in linearity.

The graph also includes text that explains the relationship between the DAC and the linearity error, stating "All eight channels shown are external reference + 5V".
